<document xml:lang="en">
    <header>
        <title>Installation on iOS (iPhone / iPad / iPod)</title>
    </header>
    <body>
        <p>After downloading the app from the App Store, your home screen could
            look like this: <br/>
            <img width="213" src="images/ios_keyboard_home_screen.en.png" alt="Home screen with Sami Keyboards"/>
        </p>
        <p>Continue as follows:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Open the app, and press the <strong>«Settings»</strong> button:<br/>
              <img width="213" src="images/ios_sami_keyboards_app.en.png" alt="The app page."/><p/>
          </li>

          <li>Select <strong>«Keyboards»</strong>:<br/>
              <img width="213" src="images/ios_keyboards.en.png"        alt="Select Keyboards"/><br/>
              Here you can also turn off key sounds if you don't like them.
              <p/>
          </li>

          <li>Enable the keyboards you want to use:<br/>
              <img width="213" src="images/ios_enable_keyboards.en.png" alt="Enable keyboards"/><p/>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <p>The installation is done!</p>

        <p>To switch to your preferred keyboard, touch and hold the globe key:</p>
        <p>
            <img width="213" src="images/ios_select_active_keyboard.en.png" alt="Keyboard selection menu"/>
        </p>

        <p>You may also just touch the globe key repeated times till you get the
            keyboard you want.</p>

    </body>
</document>
